                },
                {
                    "id": "top_complete_melt_dh_dT_dampening",
                    "description": "Top variant with complete melt and dh_dT = -10: same H_residual as `interior_complete_melt_with_residual` (953.653 W/m²), but the denominator 1 - coeff*dh_dT = 1 - 0.018*(-10) = 1.18 reduces the temperature correction. T_np1 = 273.15 + 17.1658/1.18 = 273.15 + 14.547 = 287.697 K (less warming than interior despite same H_residual — negative dh_dT indicates the surface flux decreases as T rises, providing negative feedback that damps the temperature overshoot).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "is_top": 1.0,
                        "H_i": 1000.0,
