                        {
                            "id": "T_np1_vs_H_i",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "T_np1 vs H_i (interior): flat at T_f while phase change consumes all H_i; departs below T_f (complete freeze) or above T_f (complete melt) with slope Δt/(c_i*Δz_i) = 0.018 K/(W/m²).",
                            "x": { "variable": "H_i", "label": "H_i (W/m²)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "T_np1", "label": "T_np1 (K)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "top_vs_interior_temperature_correction",
                    "description": "Compare top variant (is_top=1, dh_dT=-10) vs interior variant (is_top=0) temperature correction as a function of H_i for a dry layer (w_ice_n=0, w_liq_n=0) where H_residual = H_i. The top variant denominator 1.18 damps the temperature response by ≈15% relative to the interior variant. Surfaces the physical role of the dh_dT linearization in reducing the temperature overshoot.",
